Reasoning: The paper focuses on the performance evaluation of sparse matrix multiplication kernels on the Intel Xeon Phi coprocessor. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including numerical analysis (cs.NA), computer architecture (cs.AR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE), and mathematical software (cs.MS). However, since the paper primarily deals with the performance evaluation of numerical algorithms on a specific hardware architecture, we believe that cs.MS and cs.AR are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant, but to a lesser extent.
